properties.abstract: The Churfirsten mountains are much better known, but none of them is as close to Walensee as Nägeliberg. The vertical distance is 1700 metres, more than a mile. So, the view down to the lake and the vineyards of Quinten is breath-taking. The itinerary is as follows: from the quaint wine and fishing village of Quinten, which is only accessible by boat or on foot, the trail ascends through forest to the hay meadows of Laubegg. Then one traverses to the foot of the vertical south face of Nägeliberg. Now follows a spectacular ascent through the wild Gocht populated by ibex and chamois, and finally the itinerary leads up a steep slope and traverses the uppermost part of the south face to reach the summit. With almost 2000 metres of vertical height climbed, be proud of your achievement as a mountaineer and enjoy the view.
properties.subtitle: Uncompromising verticals to the Walensee
properties.title: Traverse from Quinten to Arvenbühl via Gocht

segments.description: From Quinten follow the marked mountain hiking trails towards Gocht. At P. 1520 before the Säls alp the white-blue marked alpine hiking trail branches off (signpost).
segments.title: Quinten - bifurcation Gocht (P. 1520)

segments.description: Follow the alpine hiking trail winding its way up Gocht. From the highest point (P. 1951) initially follow the ridge, then go eastward between boulders. The rocky ledge that blocks the direct way along the ridge, is bypassed north (left) on scree and grass. Then go southward (right) scrambling over a rocky escarpment (crux) and the uppermost ledge to reach the ridge. On the south side of the ridge a sort of grassy funnel opens. The traverse is exposed, but it is on a good grassy path. In a few minutes you reach the Nägeliberg summit on the other side of the funnel. The descent follows the north-east ridge to P. 2085, then it turns north-westward on grassy slopes. Continue pathless in hilly, arduous terrain (dolines!). T3+. Close to P. 1830 at Hinderselun you meet the white-red-white marked mountain trail (Toggenburger Höhenweg).
segments.title: Bifurcation Gocht (P. 1520) - Gocht - Nägeliberg - Alp Hinderselun

segments.description: Follow the Toggenburger Höhenweg (short re-ascent at Tritt) to Amden, Arvenbühl.
segments.title: Hinderselun - Arvenbühl

segments.description: The descent to Toggenburg makes a pretty traverse. Below Nägeliberg go north-eastward in pastures (pathless) until you meet the Toggenburger Höhenweg. Now hike (or during the summer season ride the aerial cableway) from Strichboden to Starkenbach. From Nägeliberg to Starkenbach 2–3 h, T3+.
segments.title: Variant: descent to Toggenburg
